phone\u2019s Bluetooth menu.<\/li>\n<\/ul>\n<h2>\u00a0Streaming Media through Voice Commands<\/h2>\n<p>Aside from Bluetooth, you can also stream directly using voice commands. Just say \u201cHey Google, play some jazz on Spotify,\u201d and the Home Mini will handle the rest. You can link accounts like <strong>YouTube Music, Spotify, Apple Music<\/strong>, and more.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Google Cast Support<\/h2>\n<p>The Home Mini also supports <a href=\"https:\/\/en.wikipedia.org\/wiki\/Google_Cast\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener\">Google Cast<\/a>, allowing you to stream audio from supported apps like YouTube and Netflix (audio only) using your phone or other Google Cast-enabled devices.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Limitations to Keep in Mind<\/h2>\n<p>While the Google Home Mini is versatile, it\u2019s not a high-fidelity speaker. The bass is limited, and it lacks stereo separation. For casual listening, it\u2019s great\u2014but for audiophiles, larger speakers may be a better fit.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Can It Work Without Wi-Fi?<\/h2>\n<p>Yes and no. The Home Mini requires Wi-Fi for voice assistant functions and most media playback, but once paired via Bluetooth, it can play audio without needing an internet connection.<\/p>\n<h2>\u00a0Conclusion<\/h2>\n<p>The Google Home Mini is more than just a voice assistant\u2014it can serve as a convenient Bluetooth speaker or streaming hub. Whether you\u2019re relaxing with music or amplifying your laptop audio, it\u2019s a small device with big flexibility.<\/p>\n<\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div><\/div>","protected":false},"excerpt":{"rendered":"<p>Can I Use Google Home Mini as Speaker? Yes, you can absolutely use the Google Home Mini as a speaker. Whether you&#8217;re streaming music, playing podcasts, or watching videos, this compact smart device doubles as a Bluetooth speaker for multiple use cases. \u00a0Using Google Home Mini as a Bluetooth Speaker One of the key features &#8230; <a title=\"Can i use google home mini as speaker?\" class=\"read